CURSOR RULES — SailScanner Proposal Engine

CORE PRINCIPLES
- Make minimal changes; extend existing plugins/scripts.
- Separate concerns: proposals are ss_proposal; yacht picks in proposals are ss_proposal_yacht. Do not touch yacht_charter (external, SEO-indexed). Woo remains for Trips/commerce.
- Security first: capability checks, strict REST validation, escape all output.
- No leakage: never render provider/operator names or MMK/NauSYS hosted URLs on front-end.

WORDPRESS/PLUGIN STANDARDS
- Keep all new code in a dedicated plugin folder; do not modify theme files.
- Use plugin template loader (template_include) for ss_proposal and ss_proposal_yacht templates only.
- Add noindex/nofollow via meta tag AND X-Robots-Tag header on proposal and ss_proposal_yacht pages only.
- Exclude proposals from sitemap/search/archives (Yoast/RankMath hooks if present).
- Avoid heavy dependencies; WordPress core only.

REST API REQUIREMENTS
- Reuse existing HMAC auth from sailscanner-rest-endpoints-extended.php exactly.
- Do not add a second auth system.
- Validate/sanitize payloads:
  - required: ss_yacht_data for proposal create
  - max yachts per proposal = 25
  - sanitize strings; allow limited HTML with wp_kses_post
- Use clear HTTP status codes (400/401/403/500).

DATA INTEGRITY
- Proposal yacht picks are ss_proposal_yacht posts. Never touch yacht_charter. Never render provider URLs.

TEMPLATE/UI REQUIREMENTS
- Proposal single template: portal-style with sidebar on the LEFT; sidebar fixed (sticky) on desktop; on mobile show sidebar at top or collapsible. Include a "How it works" section with steps explaining the process.
- Yacht picks rendered as cards with anchor links and WhatsApp CTA (prefilled message).
- Use accessible markup and visible focus states.
- Keep CSS lightweight and scoped to proposal/yacht templates.

LOGGING & DEBUG
- Add SAILSCANNER_PROPOSALS_DEBUG constant.
- Log non-sensitive operational info only; never log PII in plain text.

PERFORMANCE
- Do not sideload images in v1; store and render remote URLs.
- Avoid expensive meta queries on every page load; cache token lookups if needed.
- Limit REST payload size and request frequency.

DELIVERABLE HYGIENE
- Provide README notes:
  - how to call endpoints
  - how to run python importer
  - how to rotate HMAC secrets/keys
- Add basic sanity handling: missing/invalid token -> 404 or friendly expired message.
